text: Oskar Baker (born 25 May 1998) is a professional Australian rules footballer playing for the Melbourne Football Club in the Australian Football League (AFL). He attended Padua College in Brisbane and played for Aspley in the North East Australian Football League before being drafted by Melbourne with the 48th selection in the 2017 national draft.
